    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-01T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-01T04:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5034 China—Searchlight Publishing Co./20:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1" type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-01T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 1, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 1—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>357. Department’s 230, July 30, 9 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>] p.m. Department’s
                    cable is very much garbled but believe amplification by [<hi rend="italic"
                        >my?</hi>] 353, July 29, 5 p.m.<note n="20" xml:id="d732fn20">Not
                        printed.</note> furnishes information desired. <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> was called into the Consulate
                    General and in the presence of District Attorney <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_SG1">Sellett</persName> and Consul <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_SRL1">Smyth</persName> I read <hi rend="italic">in
                        extenso</hi> and verbatim Department’s 223, July 20, 4 p.m., to <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName>. I made few comments though
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SG1">Sellett</persName> commented,
                    enlarging upon the previous conversations with <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> and he explained <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName>’ report that he had made in
                    the <hi rend="italic">Forum</hi> of previous interview. To my astonishment the
                    local press carried, apparently upon <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1"
                        >Isaacs</persName>’ apparent statement, an incorrect interpretation of the
                    interview.</p>
                <p>I am of the opinion that he intended to seek notoriety and sympathy.</p>
                <p>There has never been any mention made of his personally being deprived of
                    extraterritorial rights.</p>
                <p>As a precaution I made this morning an appointment with the Mayor for tomorrow
                    when I intend to give to him in Confidence a copy of my statement to <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> and verbally to warn the
                    Mayor that there was no intention to waive the extraterritorial rights that
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> has.</p>
                <p>Through the <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> and its correspondent in
                    Shanghai his father has urged <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1"
                        >Isaacs</persName> to return to the United States. <persName
                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_IHR1">Isaacs</persName> has replied that he “did not
                    believe in turning the other cheek or showing his heels to the enemy.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
